{"questionId":"7570","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A lighting system consists of two long metal rods with a potential difference maintained&nbsp;between them. Identical lamps can be connected between the rods as required.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/9d199c57b4ecb64a08530bfe8e48faefd54cba6d.png\"></p>\n<p>The following data are available for the lamps when at their working temperature.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:90px;\">Lamp specifications&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 24 V, 5.0 W</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:90px;\">Power supply emf&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;24 V</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:90px;\">Power supply maximum current&nbsp; &nbsp;8.0 A</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:90px;\">Length of each rod&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;12.5 m</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:90px;\">Resistivity of rod metal&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;7.2 × 10<sup>–7</sup> Ω m</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Each rod is to have a resistance no greater than 0.10 Ω. Calculate, in m, the minimum&nbsp;radius of each rod. Give your answer to an appropriate number of significant figures.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 1:</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r = \\sqrt {\\frac{{\\rho l}}{{\\pi {\\text{R}}}}} \">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>ρ</mi>\n        <mi>l</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>R</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span> <em><strong>OR&nbsp;</strong></em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{7.2 \\times {{10}^{ - 7}} \\times 12.5}}{{\\pi&nbsp; \\times 0.1}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>7.2</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>7</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mn>12.5</mn>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mn>0.1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p><em>r</em> = 5.352 × 10<sup>−3</sup> ✔</p>\n<p>5.4 × 10<sup>−3&nbsp;</sup>«m» ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>For MP2 accept any SF </em></p>\n<p><em>For MP3 accept only 2 SF </em></p>\n<p><em>For MP3 accept <strong>ANY</strong> answer given to 2 SF</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 2:</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A = \\frac{{7.2 \\times {{10}^{ - 7}} \\times 12.5}}{{0.1}}\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7.2</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>7</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>12.5</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p><em>r</em>&nbsp;= 5.352&nbsp;× 10<sup>−3</sup>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>5.4&nbsp;× 10<sup>−3&nbsp;</sup>«m» ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>For MP2 accept any SF </em></p>\n<p><em>For MP3 accept only 2 SF </em></p>\n<p><em>For MP3 accept <strong>ANY</strong> answer given to 2 SF</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"7570","referenceCode":"18N.2.HL.TZ0.2a","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Each rod is to have a resistance no greater than 0.10 Ω. Calculate, in m, the minimum radius of each rod. Give your answer to an appropriate number of significant figures.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.2 – Heating effect of electric currents","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","1.1 – Measurements in physics","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}